author: By     MarketWatch
title: Nymex oil futures close at lowest level in more than 4 months
text:
West Texas Intermediate crude oil for September delivery CLU5, +0.13% on Nymex fell 59 cents, or 1.3%, to end at $45.15 a barrel on Wednesday, the lowest settlement for a most-active contract since March. Oil futures gave up early gains. A fall in weekly U.S. crude inventories was offset by a rise in supplies of gasoline and other products, while a stronger dollar also weighed on the market.
Read the full story: Oil rebound sours as crude drops to 4-month low
